article.headline: Robert Morris crushes Wagner 91-59
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Rodney Pryor led four players in double figures with 25 points and Robert Morris crushed Wagner 91-59 on Thursday night. Pryor was 7 of 10 from the field with five 3-pointers. Marcquise Reed had 20 points on 8-of-16 shooting, while Lucky Jones added 15 and Elijah Minnie 13. The Colonials had 13 steals and were 14 of 22 beyond the arc. Robert Morris (15-14, 11-6 Northeast) used a 14-2 run early in the game, and a 12-point spurt later in the half, to open a 44-29 lead at the break. The lead hit 20 on Pryor's layup 2:02 into the second half and Lucky Jones' 3-pointer with 9:14 left pushed the advantage over the 30-point mark. Wagner (10-18, 8-9) was led by Corey Henson with 10 points. The Seahawks shot 31 percent, though they won the rebound battle at 42-34 with 22 offensive boards.
